name: achilles tendonitis
desc: Inflammation or irritation of Achilles tendon caused by repetitive loading or excessive strain.

name: bursitis
desc: Inflammation of joint cushioning sacs due to repeated friction or pressure.

name: calf muscle strain
desc: Overstretching or tearing of the calf muscle fibers due to excessive load or sudden movement.

name: chondromalacia
desc: Cartilage softening under kneecap causing painful knee movement.

name: compartment syndrome
desc: Increased pressure within muscle compartments restricting blood flow from trauma or intense exertion.

name: cyst
desc: Fluid-filled sac formed by repetitive friction or tissue irritation.

name: deformity
desc: Chronic abnormal structural changes in toes or foot joints due to biomechanical stress.

name: disc degeneration
desc: Breakdown and gradual loss of spinal disc cushioning due to repeated loading or aging.

name: disc protrusion
desc: Spinal disc bulging that presses against nerve roots from excessive spinal loading.

name: dislocation
desc: Bones in a joint lose alignment due to severe force or biomechanical disruption.

name: fibula fracture
desc: Break in fibula from direct trauma or excessive rotational stress.

name: fibula stress fracture
desc: Small cracks in the fibula caused by repeated stress and loading.

name: first ray tendonitis (turf toe)
desc: Inflammation of tendons at the base of big toe from forced upward bending.

name: gastrocnemius strain
desc: Overstretching or tearing of calf muscle due to sudden load or rapid movement.

name: groin muscle strain
desc: Tearing or overstretching of muscles in groin due to sudden or excessive load.

name: hamstring muscle strain
desc: Overstretching or tearing of the hamstring muscles at the back of thigh due to excessive force or rapid movement.

name: no injury
desc: No injury has been diagnosed.

name: high ankle sprain with tendonosis
desc: Sprain and chronic degeneration of tendons above ankle from rotational mechanical stress.

name: hip flexor strain
desc: Overstretching or tearing of muscles that flex the hip, typically from rapid or forceful movements.

name: hip joint irritation
desc: Pain and inflammation in the hip joint from repetitive mechanical stress.

name: ischial bursitis
desc: Inflammation of cushioning sacs at sitting bones due to prolonged sitting or repetitive stress.

name: itb syndrome
desc: Painful friction of iliotibial band rubbing over knee joint from repetitive bending movements.

name: labral tear
desc: Damage to cartilage rim (labrum) around joint socket from excessive mechanical stress or injury.

name: ligament sprain
desc: Stretching or tearing of ligaments due to excessive force or abnormal joint movement.

name: ligament tear/rupture acl
desc: Complete or partial tear of anterior knee ligament from twisting or pivoting stress.

name: ligament tear/rupture mcl
desc: Tearing or rupture of medial knee ligament caused by lateral mechanical force.

name: ligament tear/rupture pcl
desc: Tearing of posterior knee ligament typically from direct impact or hyperextension.

name: low back pain
desc: Pain from mechanical stress, instability, or muscle imbalance in lower spine.

name: medial tibial stress syndrome
desc: Inflammation along inner shin bone from repetitive force, commonly known as shin splints.

name: meniscal tear-lateral
desc: Outer knee cartilage injury caused by twisting or abnormal biomechanical loading.

name: meniscal tear-medial
desc: Injury of the inner knee cartilage from twisting or repetitive stress.

name: metarsalgia
desc: Pain in ball of foot caused by excessive pressure on metatarsal bones.

name: metatarsal stress fracture
desc: Small cracks in foot bones due to repetitive impact or stress.

name: muscle spasm
desc: Involuntary muscle contraction due to fatigue or biomechanical stress response.

name: muscle strain
desc: Muscle fibers stretched or torn due to excessive or sudden mechanical load.

name: motor vehicle accident
desc: Biomechanical injury sustained from motor vehicle accident unrelated to running.

name: nerve impingement
desc: Pressure on a nerve caused by mechanical compression or tight tissues.

name: osteoarthritis
desc: Degeneration of joint cartilage causing bone friction and inflammation.

name: osteitis pubis
desc: Inflammation at pubic symphysis from repetitive pelvic stress or instability.

name: other
desc: Unspecified injury or pain without clear categorization.

name: pain
desc: General sensation of discomfort  without specific injury details.

name: patellar fracture
desc: Broken kneecap due to direct trauma or excessive biomechanical loading.

name: patellofemoral pain syndrome
desc: Pain around kneecap caused by poor tracking and mechanical friction of kneecap (patellofemoral pain syndrome).

name: patellar tendonitis
desc: Inflammation of tendon connecting kneecap to shinbone from repetitive stress.

name: pelvic dysfunction general
desc: General instability or alignment issues in pelvic region affecting biomechanics.

name: pelvic malalignment
desc: Misalignment or imbalance of pelvic bones causing uneven biomechanical loading.

name: peroneal tendonitis
desc: Inflammation of tendons around the outer ankle due to repetitive stress.

name: pes anserine bursitis
desc: Inflammation of bursa on inner knee from repetitive knee bending movements.

name: piriformis syndrome
desc: Compression of sciatic nerve due to tightening or spasm of piriformis muscle.

name: plantar fasciitis
desc: Inflammation and pain of plantar fascia tissue on bottom of foot due to repetitive stress or overload.

name: plica
desc: Inflammation and irritation of tissue fold within knee joint due to repetitive movement.

name: sciatic nerve impingement
desc: Compression of sciatic nerve due to mechanical pressure causing radiating pain.

name: shin splints
desc: Stress injury to muscles and tissues along shin from repetitive impact and loading.

name: si joint pain
desc: Pain due to misalignment or excessive strain at sacroiliac joint.

name: strain
desc: Overstretching or tearing of muscles or tendons due to mechanical overload.

name: stress fracture
desc: Tiny cracks in bone from repeated mechanical stress exceeding bone strength.

name: stress reaction
desc: Bone irritation preceding fracture caused by repetitive mechanical loading.

name: synovitis
desc: Inflammation of joint lining due to repetitive mechanical irritation.

name: tendonitis
desc: Inflammation of tendon caused by repetitive stress or excessive mechanical load.

name: tibia fracture
desc: Complete break in shin bone from trauma or excessive mechanical force.

name: tibia stress fracture
desc: Small cracks in tibia caused by repetitive mechanical overload.
